reviewText: An entertaining overview of the eastern Canada Maritime Provinces.  If one has an interest in this area, this short one-hour DVD will give a good overview of that area of Canada.
No stars! I couldn't even see the video it was so blurry!!
The feed on Prime was terrible. Very grainy and couldn't make out anything of interest. We tried to upload several times with the same results .
Video was pixillated and picture could not be adjusted to TV screen. Still, we enjoyed the video as preparation for possible tour of Canada but you really cannot view the film properly.
I expected the dvd to be playable on a dvd player. This dvd only works on my lap top (not my dvd player).
Well done and interesting, however, the video quality was poor
The video quality is unwatchable.  Doesn't even worth the $2.
This is a low budget film that poorly displays the beauty of Eastern Canada. The video kept buffering making it hard to watch.
The documentary was very good, but the quality of the video was very low.
Charming, youthful guide, ZoeDAmato, does an outstanding job taking you along on her adventure. Fast paced, good maps, history, geography, beautiful scenery, and a lot of fun.
